<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sounds like wishful thinking at best.<P>There is a self-only treeform spell that druids get post-50 that has a clarity effect in it, but I can only imagine the flamestorm that would hit Whineplay if they gave druids any sort of mana-regen ability at lower levels.<P>------------------<BR>Relbeek Einre<BR>35th level (no, I don't say 'season') Druid<BR>Rivervale, Brell Serilis</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Islana Soulkiss
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You get a self-only wolf form at level 54 called Form of the Howler.  This has a mana regen effect added with the penalty of not getting any ATK bonus for the form.  My closest estimate is that it seems to roughly equal Breeze for mana regen, which helps more than it sounds as you run around outdoors hunting/tracking.   <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"></FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Customer
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Personally, I'd rather trade off an atk bonus for a breeze/clarity like spell. Less downtime = more kiting = more killing = more XP. <P>therefore more fun.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Shanya
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You will never, ever, ever get any kind of clarity on low level druids  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">  Druids and Necromancers are already very well balanced (what other classes call overpowered), and course if you start giving other classes clarity-like effects (bards get their mana song at 32, necro's get better than clarity mana regen from lvl 8) it will start to detract from the Enchanter class somewhat.<P>Form of the Howler add a clarity like effect as a post 50 spell, but as most 50's will tell you, with that much mana Clarity is wearing a bit thin for mana regen.<P>Shanya Wolfreaver,<BR>36th level Druid<BR>Innoruuk Server</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
