<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">actually , as a necro (only level 18) I have found that breeze/clarity is better than the HP to MANA trade that necros get. <P>and no, I don't think that level 50s will tell you any clarity/breeze effect isn't worth much. Wanna know why? Cuz the spells cost a crap load of mana at that time. ANYTHING and I mean ANYTHING that grants mana regen is usually accepted for casters. <P>My level 47 wizard friend is always asking for clarity, or breeze. Trust me no one likes downtime. </FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Shanya
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually this is true of the lvl 8 spell which only converts a small amount of mana to HP each tick, the higher level necro spells offer superior convertion rates.  Try getting a 'chanter stick Clarity on you with a higher level spell on, it just won't stick as EQ's buff-comparison check will reject clarity as being the weaker buff.<P>As for clarity at high levels, try it on a 53 character with 201 INT and +100 MANA (or more), Clarity is barely percievable at that level, adding only a fraction of your natural mana regen.  Thats where my comment of "wearing a bit thin" comes from, I did not say "not worth much" - any bonus is a plus, but it's wearing so thin that you are hard pushed to notice it's effects; like sticking regen on a lvl 60 troll warrior   <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/wink.gif"><P>Shanya Wolfreaver<BR>37th level Druid<BR>Innoruuk Server<p>[This message has been edited by Shanya (edited November 09, 2000).]</FONT>
