</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, I'm a 21st level Druid and I stumbled across a rare spell around level 9.  The spell is called Summon Ally: Enchanter.  It's a pet spell (most people don't think Druids get pets!) and it summons an enchanter of your level, give or take 5 levels.  And if you can summon a 16th level Enchanter, they'll Breeze you!<P>The AI on these pets seems to be a bit iffy.  Some have excellent AI, and are capable of dealing with several mobs at once, keeping them from killing you.  Others seem to get the AI for the Summon Ally: Wizard spell, and get themselves killed often.<P>There isn't usually a material component needed for these spells (there's a whole line of them), and generally your pet will be extremely loyal and well-behaved if you can keep it's health up.  It works wonders in conjunction with Summon Ally: Tank, too.   <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/tongue.gif"><P>Daeddwin Proudfoot<BR>21st Level Lowbie Halfling Druid<BR>Spirit of Norrath, Lanys T'yvl</FONT>
